In this article, President Donald Trump addresses five deployed units from each branch of the armed forces via video teleconference from Mar-a-Lago Club and Resort in Palm Beach, Florida. He expresses his gratitude for their service and acknowledges their bravery and dedication to defending freedom. Trump specifically mentions the First Brigade Combat Team of the 82nd Airborne, the Marine Corps Special Operations, the sailors aboard the USS Monterey, the 74th Expeditionary Fighter Squadron, and the Coasties aboard the Cutter Wrangell. He commends their progress in fighting against ISIS and assures them that they have the support and love of the American people. Trump also mentions the positive changes in the country, such as the strong economy and the upcoming tax cuts. He concludes by thanking the military families for their sacrifices and asks the press to leave so he can have confidential conversations with the deployed units.